                                <div class="order-2 lg:col-span-4">
                                    <h3 class="font-lora text-primary text-[22px] xl:text-lg capitalize mb-2">The Turkish Passport</h3>
                                    <p class="mb-4 ">The Turkish passport is a powerful travel document that ranks 37th in the world in terms of travel freedom, according to the 2023 Visa Guide Passport statistics. This means that it provides its holder with an overall average degree of mobility. It offers a range of advantages to its holders, including:
                                    </p>
                                    <ul class="ml-[40px] list-disc">
                                        <li>The property must cost $400,000.</li>
                                        <li>Only one person can own the property to be eligible for Turkish citizenship.</li>
                                        <li>The nationality of the investor should not be among the five nationalities prohibited from obtaining citizenship through buying property, which are Syrian, Armenian, North Korean, Cuban, and Cypriot, except for Turkish Cypriots.</li>
                                        <li>The value of the property cannot be divided among more than one owner; only the owner who obtains the Turkish citizenship.</li>
                                        <li>The desired property for obtaining Turkish citizenship should not be in a security or military zone.</li>
                                        <li>The required property size for the citizenship matter and properties should not exceed 10% of the area in which it is located.</li>
                                        <li>Payment for the property must be made through regular bank transfers.</li>
                                        <li>Ensure that the real estate appraisal process is completed through a government-approved real estate valuation company.</li>
                                        <li>This property cannot be sold before a period of 3 years, and that is through an official commitment not to sell.</li>
                                        <li>Documenting the purchase process through the official government-affiliated land registry office called "the land registry".</li>
                                        <li>Provide all necessary documentation to prove the purchase process, including bank transfer information.</li>
                                        <li>Submit an application to the Immigration Office and General Directorate of Population and Citizenship Affairs.</li>
                                        <li>Visit the Citizenship Information Office in Istanbul or Ankara to complete the citizenship process within 6-7 months.</li>
                                        <li>The spouse and children under legal age will be granted Turkish citizenship upon application.</li>
                                        <li>There are several ways to obtain Turkish citizenship through investment, such as depositing $500,000 in a Turkish bank and not withdrawing it for 3 years, purchasing government bonds for the same amount and holding them for 3 years, investing $500,000 in fixed assets under the supervision of the Ministry of Industry and Technology, or providing 50 job opportunities within Turkey as the owner of a company and providing necessary documentation, including legal registration of the company in the country, employee insurance, and a safe work environment, all under the supervision of the Ministry of Labour and Social Security.</li>
                                    </ul>
